# genericrequest
Attempt to add a generic method for sending requests to solr. Solr setups may 
consist of various customized requesthandlers that are not coverable by this 
extension. The current approach is to add an additional genericRequest() method
to the SolrClient that internally uses SolrClient::GENERIC_SERVLET_TYPE to send
the requests to. The servlet can be configured via SolrClient::setServlet(). 

Example: 
  // client
  $client = new SolrClient($cfg); 
  
  // set servlet to desired destination 
  // request url will be built pointing to http://host:port/path/servlet/
  // host,port and path are configuration parameters for SolrClient
  $client->setServlet(SolrClient::GENERIC_SERVLET_TYPE, 'suggest');
  
  // QueryObject
  // Since QueryObject is a SolrParams class, generic
  // getters and setters are available for the parameters. 
  $prms = new SolrQuery();
  $prms->set('spellcheck', 'true');
  $prms->set('spellcheck.extendedResults', 'true');
  $prms->set('q', 'ca.*');
  $prms->set('spellcheck.dictionary', 'suggest');
  $prms->set('spellcheck.count', 1000);
  $prms->set('spellcheck.build', 'true');
  
  $resp = $client->requestGeneric($prms);
   

Even though this seems to work, i could imagine finding a better
solution for generic requests without interferring with the internal
servlet/request structure.
